          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Two sample were mounted in the center of vacuum clamber",
                "back-to-back on support plate.",
                "B-10 sample - to monitor neutron beam by (n,alpha) .",
                "Cm-oxide sample of 141+-3 microg, deposited on Al",
                "30 microm backing, of 15 mm diameter.",
                "Isotopic composition:",
                "Isotope    Number of Atoms       At.%",
                "Cm-244      3.11x10**15           0.901",
                "Cm-245      3.41x10**17          98.685",
                "Cm-246      1.40x10**15           0.404",
                "Cm-247      2.75x10**15           0.008",
                "Cm-248      6.85x10**15           0.002",
                "U-235 99.94% enriched sample, with a diameter of 15 mm",
                ",mass of (193.29+1.33)microg, deposited on a 30 microm",
                "thick Al backing; used to determine neutron flux and",
                "detection efficiency."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Deviation of a 1/v behavior is given by the so-called",
                "Westcott factor, which depends on the temperature of",
                "the neutron spectrum. The Westcott factors for U-235 =",
                "0.9772+0.0008 and for Cm-245 = 0.954+0.033 were used",
                "from REL-REF of S.F.Mughabghab.",
                "Our result overlaps within the error bars with the",
                "previous results and it shows a deviation of about 6%",
                "from the value adopted by the nuclear data libraries."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "For 1.6% contribution from SF to the spectrum.",
                "For 2.6% contribution from the epithermal component to",
                "the (n,f) spectrum."
              ]
            }
          ],
